pbCfgTable.name: pbCfgTable
pbCfgTable.description: A table containing an configuration information for each Gateway NAC in the NAS chassis.

pbCfgEntry.name: pbCfgEntry
pbCfgEntry.description: There is one Configuration row for each Gateway Card in the NAS chassis.

pbCfgIndex.name: pbCfgIndex
pbCfgIndex.description: A unique value for each Gateway Card in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding Gateway Card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

pbCfgMaxSessions.name: pbCfgMaxSessions
pbCfgMaxSessions.description: This read-only object defines the maximum number of packet bus sessions supported by this entity. This value is used to determine the number of rows present in the pbSessionTable for this entity.

pbSessionTable.name: pbSessionTable
pbSessionTable.description: The Packet Bus Session table contains an entry for each manageable Gateway NAC in the chassis. It provides a means to configure packet bus connections and determine the status of the defined connections. This table resides in the NAC and can be impemented as either a dense or sparse table.

pbSessionEntry.name: pbSessionEntry
pbSessionEntry.description: There is an row for each Packet Bus connection.

pbSessionEntityIndex.name: pbSessionEntityIndex
pbSessionEntityIndex.description: A unique value for each entity in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

pbSessionIndex.name: pbSessionIndex
pbSessionIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the packet bus session for this entity.

pbSessionDestSlot.name: pbSessionDestSlot
pbSessionDestSlot.description: A number that identifies the slot of the entity in the chassis to which a packet bus session has been assigned.

pbSessionDestChan.name: pbSessionDestChan
pbSessionDestChan.description: A number that identifies a particular entity in a slot.

pbSessionDestSess.name: pbSessionDestSess
pbSessionDestSess.description: A number that identifies the particular session from the other communicating Gateway.

pbSessionRowState.name: pbSessionRowState
pbSessionRowState.description: Set availability for this row of packet bus session. Default=free(1).

pbSessionStatus.name: pbSessionStatus
pbSessionStatus.description: Displays the current status of the packet bus session. A status of Unassigned coupled with a state of used indicates that a packet bus failure has occured.

pbSessionReqStatus.name: pbSessionReqStatus
pbSessionReqStatus.description: Used to assign or delete a session between the entities specified by the table indecies. A request connect is a issue of packet bus session link start, and a request disconnect is a issue of packet bus session link terminate. Default=disconnected(1).

pbSessionLastRequest.name: pbSessionLastRequest
pbSessionLastRequest.description: Indicates the type of communications contained in the last packet sent to the destination entity.

pbSessionPktSents.name: pbSessionPktSents
pbSessionPktSents.description: A counter that indicates number of packets that have been sent.

pbSessionPktRcvds.name: pbSessionPktRcvds
pbSessionPktRcvds.description: A counter that indicates number of packets that have been received.

pbSessionPktSize.name: pbSessionPktSize
pbSessionPktSize.description: A number that indicates the packet size of the current or last established session.

pbSessionBusTimeOuts.name: pbSessionBusTimeOuts
pbSessionBusTimeOuts.description: A counter that indicates number of packet bus timeout that have occurred.

pbSessionErrorStatus.name: pbSessionErrorStatus
pbSessionErrorStatus.description: Error return status from last packet command.

pbTrapEnaTable.name: pbTrapEnaTable
pbTrapEnaTable.description: A table containing an enable for each trap that a manageable Gateway entity is capable of generating.

pbTrapEnaEntry.name: pbTrapEnaEntry
pbTrapEnaEntry.description: There is one Gateway trap enable row for each Gateway card in the NAS chassis.

pbTrapEnaIndex.name: pbTrapEnaIndex
pbTrapEnaIndex.description: A unique value for each Gateway Card in the chassis. The value of this object matches the value of the index of the corresponding Gateway Card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

pbTrapSessionIndex.name: pbTrapSessionIndex
pbTrapSessionIndex.description: A value that identifies the packet bus session for trap enable/disable.

pbTrapEnaSessActive.name: pbTrapEnaSessActive
pbTrapEnaSessActive.description: An object which enables or disables the Active Session trap.

pbTrapEnaPktBusCongest.name: pbTrapEnaPktBusCongest
pbTrapEnaPktBusCongest.description: An object to enable or disable the Packet Bus Congestion trap. The Packet Bus Congestion trap is generated when a valid packet bus session is in progress but either the Modem or the Gateway packet bus driver is experiencing congestion problem.

pbTrapEnaPktBusSessLost.name: pbTrapEnaPktBusSessLost
pbTrapEnaPktBusSessLost.description: An object to enable or disable the trap that is generated when a valid Packet Bus session has been lost.

pbTrapEnaSessionInactive.name: pbTrapEnaSessionInactive
pbTrapEnaSessionInactive.description: An object to enable or disable a trap which is generated when a request is made to change a packet bus session from the active to inactive state.

pbTrapEnaSessionError.name: pbTrapEnaSessionError
pbTrapEnaSessionError.description: An object which enables or disables the packet bus session error trap.
